1
00:00:10,480 --> 00:00:11,880
=The Quirky and The Charming=

2
00:01:19,180 --> 00:01:23,660
=Episode 7=

3
00:01:28,960 --> 00:01:30,680
So you came all the way here

4
00:01:30,760 --> 00:01:31,800
just to pick on us?

5
00:01:32,688 --> 00:01:35,440
Of course I have to be cautious
when picking a business partner.

6
00:01:37,480 --> 00:01:38,240
Sorry about this.

7
00:01:38,533 --> 00:01:40,600
We intended to let you all
clinch a deal with TY.

8
00:01:41,160 --> 00:01:43,160
But you know this too.
They have high standards.

9
00:01:43,160 --> 00:01:45,270
They insisted on
working with Bright Platinum Hotel.

10
00:01:45,320 --> 00:01:46,800
I couldn't refuse their invitation.

11
00:01:47,520 --> 00:01:48,360
But don't worry.

12
00:01:49,080 --> 00:01:51,880
With our ties, I'll make sure you
do good when I'm doing good.

13
00:01:51,880 --> 00:01:53,600
The tea here is pretty nice.

14
00:01:54,520 --> 00:01:55,160
Next,

15
00:01:55,160 --> 00:01:56,600
they have a three-week training.

16
00:01:56,680 --> 00:01:57,760
I plan to hold it here.

17
00:01:59,560 --> 00:02:02,040
So, you intend to work
with your competitor?

18
00:02:02,760 --> 00:02:03,520
Competitor?

19
00:02:04,222 --> 00:02:06,720
To put it more accurately,
it's a rival who has lost to us.

20
00:02:07,600 --> 00:02:08,160
Alright.

21
00:02:08,400 --> 00:02:09,640
Reserve the banquet hall for me.

22
00:02:10,080 --> 00:02:12,240
The details of the collaboration
are documented here.

23
00:02:12,288 --> 00:02:13,866
Tell your legal department to review it.

24
00:02:16,680 --> 00:02:17,720
There's one thing

25
00:02:18,200 --> 00:02:19,880
I don't understand and am curious about.

26
00:02:20,800 --> 00:02:23,160
Since Bright Platinum is so great,

27
00:02:23,600 --> 00:02:24,880
why did Mr. Lin Jr.

28
00:02:25,400 --> 00:02:26,960
choose to stay at Spring Sea, then?

29
00:02:35,920 --> 00:02:36,480
Alright.

30
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:39,440
You can talk to Ms. Man
regarding the collaboration.

31
00:02:39,533 --> 00:02:41,666
I have something else to do.
I'll make a move first.

32
00:02:43,960 --> 00:02:44,960
I'm not done yet.

33
00:02:46,040 --> 00:02:46,440
I...

34
00:02:51,640 --> 00:02:54,160
The coffee here is pretty special.

35
00:02:55,080 --> 00:02:56,680
I prefer the texture of the coffee here.

36
00:02:56,800 --> 00:02:57,800
It's slightly sour.

37
00:02:58,533 --> 00:02:59,800
It's not too bitter too.

38
00:03:00,400 --> 00:03:00,880
It's...

39
00:03:04,200 --> 00:03:06,400
Mr. Lin Jr., you have
a unique preference indeed.

40
00:03:06,555 --> 00:03:08,400
You chose to collaborate
with Bright Platinum,

41
00:03:08,400 --> 00:03:09,733
yet you're staying at Spring Sea.

42
00:03:09,920 --> 00:03:10,440
What's wrong?

43
00:03:10,840 --> 00:03:12,280
Are you keeping your mistress here?

44
00:03:12,880 --> 00:03:13,440
That's right.

45
00:03:13,666 --> 00:03:14,680
How did you find out?

46
00:03:16,560 --> 00:03:17,200
I guess so.

47
00:03:18,177 --> 00:03:20,220
After all, Bright Platinum
is grand and glamorous.

48
00:03:20,240 --> 00:03:21,400
You can't hide anyone there.

49
00:03:24,600 --> 00:03:25,400
You can have it.

50
00:03:37,640 --> 00:03:39,400
Don't tell me he's going to jump?

51
00:03:40,120 --> 00:03:42,240
Why don't we help him out?

52
00:03:42,480 --> 00:03:43,240
We mustn't.

53
00:03:43,840 --> 00:03:45,120
We should wait for Boss.

54
00:03:46,080 --> 00:03:48,000
No one is as much
of a laughing stock as me!

55
00:03:49,280 --> 00:03:50,960
She was actually a divorcee!

56
00:03:51,960 --> 00:03:52,520
Ran?

57
00:03:53,400 --> 00:03:55,520
Why did that happen?

58
00:03:55,600 --> 00:03:57,080
Why me?

59
00:03:57,440 --> 00:03:58,800
Why?

60
00:03:59,422 --> 00:04:00,680
Do you know the era you're in?

61
00:04:00,800 --> 00:04:02,080
Divorce isn't that big of a deal.

62
00:04:02,240 --> 00:04:03,280
You shouldn't dwell on it.

63
00:04:03,680 --> 00:04:04,760
Don't try anything silly.

64
00:04:04,960 --> 00:04:06,840
She deceived me!

65
00:04:06,960 --> 00:04:08,160
To think that I trusted her.

66
00:04:09,280 --> 00:04:09,720
I...

67
00:04:11,280 --> 00:04:12,360
I should take my own life!

68
00:04:12,400 --> 00:04:14,177
You want to take your life
because of this?

69
00:04:14,400 --> 00:04:15,080
Don't stop me!

70
00:04:15,088 --> 00:04:16,711
You should let me take my life instead.

71
00:04:28,720 --> 00:04:30,560
Your wife was just a divorcee.

72
00:04:31,480 --> 00:04:32,240
But me?

73
00:04:33,320 --> 00:04:35,400
I only found out
that my husband has a wife

74
00:04:35,920 --> 00:04:37,480
on our wedding day.

75
00:04:37,688 --> 00:04:38,360
Impossible.

76
00:04:38,440 --> 00:04:39,560
Who said so?

77
00:04:42,880 --> 00:04:46,280
That darned Li Lei.

78
00:04:47,440 --> 00:04:49,040
Not only does he have a wife,

79
00:04:49,520 --> 00:04:50,800
but he also has twins.

80
00:04:50,960 --> 00:04:53,080
They're old enough to run errands now.

81
00:04:55,160 --> 00:04:56,960
I served him for so many years.

82
00:04:57,720 --> 00:04:59,760
I devoted my youth to him.

83
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:02,560
Everything was in vain!

84
00:05:02,760 --> 00:05:05,800
That's what you called being deceived!

85
00:05:06,400 --> 00:05:07,520
Is your fate worse than mine?

86
00:05:08,120 --> 00:05:09,280
Just let me die!

87
00:05:09,720 --> 00:05:10,640
You mustn't.

88
00:05:10,800 --> 00:05:11,520
If you die now...

89
00:05:11,600 --> 00:05:12,280
Don't stop me!

90
00:05:12,311 --> 00:05:13,970
- Just let me die!
- It's not worth it.

91
00:05:14,520 --> 00:05:15,760
You mustn't do it.

92
00:05:15,880 --> 00:05:16,920
Think about it.

93
00:05:17,320 --> 00:05:19,080
If you jump off because of a scum,

94
00:05:19,080 --> 00:05:20,120
it's not worth it at all.

95
00:05:20,400 --> 00:05:21,800
Come. You should get down for now.

96
00:05:22,444 --> 00:05:23,369
Let's talk this over.

97
00:05:23,370 --> 00:05:24,933
I won't jump. You shouldn't jump either.

98
00:05:24,933 --> 00:05:25,840
Let's talk this over.

99
00:05:25,920 --> 00:05:27,933
I'm sure there's a way
to overcome the obstacle.

100
00:05:28,440 --> 00:05:29,080
Tell me.

101
00:05:29,920 --> 00:05:32,400
Why are we so pitiful?

102
00:05:33,280 --> 00:05:34,960
We share the same fate.

103
00:05:35,200 --> 00:05:36,360
How can you compare to me?

104
00:05:36,920 --> 00:05:38,360
You're so lucky.

105
00:05:38,600 --> 00:05:39,560
You see, a divorce

106
00:05:39,644 --> 00:05:42,511
is a negative review left
on one's life when they choose partners.

107
00:05:43,360 --> 00:05:45,360
She still chose to get married to you

108
00:05:45,560 --> 00:05:47,080
after getting divorced

109
00:05:47,240 --> 00:05:48,360
because she trusted you.

110
00:05:48,440 --> 00:05:49,240
She trusted you.

111
00:05:49,360 --> 00:05:51,840
That's why she believed in love again.

112
00:05:52,644 --> 00:05:54,680
You have no idea how much
she has been through

113
00:05:54,760 --> 00:05:55,880
during this process.

114
00:05:56,560 --> 00:05:57,000
But...

115
00:05:57,440 --> 00:06:00,160
She could've told me
about it earlier, right?

116
00:06:00,320 --> 00:06:01,520
She should've...

117
00:06:01,577 --> 00:06:02,800
You were together for so long.

118
00:06:02,800 --> 00:06:03,960
Don't you understand why?

119
00:06:05,088 --> 00:06:06,920
Was she afraid
that I might take it to heart?

120
00:06:07,560 --> 00:06:08,680
Maybe it's because

121
00:06:09,280 --> 00:06:10,720
she doesn't want to lose you.

122
00:06:15,240 --> 00:06:17,040
Back then, I proposed to her

123
00:06:17,160 --> 00:06:18,560
in this very room.

124
00:06:20,080 --> 00:06:22,160
I truly love her.

125
00:06:25,120 --> 00:06:27,280
I love her a lot, you know?

126
00:06:27,280 --> 00:06:29,520
He's married, he has twins,

127
00:06:29,777 --> 00:06:31,755
and they're old enough to run errands?

128
00:06:32,600 --> 00:06:34,360
Isn't she describing Boss?

129
00:06:37,911 --> 00:06:39,400
Did Yi Ran jump off the building?

130
00:06:40,760 --> 00:06:42,960
She's so pitiful.

131
00:06:46,320 --> 00:06:47,040
Let go of him.

132
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:50,960
Let go of him!

133
00:06:52,777 --> 00:06:53,800
I'm not talking to you.

134
00:06:53,960 --> 00:06:55,120
Who told her to mess around?

135
00:06:57,320 --> 00:06:59,120
This mister suffered a breakdown

136
00:06:59,280 --> 00:07:00,600
because of his relationship.

137
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:01,800
Now, he's fine.

138
00:07:01,844 --> 00:07:02,977
I was referring to you.

139
00:07:04,022 --> 00:07:05,577
Did you say I was messing around?

140
00:07:10,644 --> 00:07:12,222
Did you guys actually take alcohol?

141
00:07:13,440 --> 00:07:16,440
Sometimes, we need different methods
to resolve issues.

142
00:07:16,644 --> 00:07:18,040
Don't mind the details too much.

143
00:07:18,800 --> 00:07:20,080
You've let me down utterly.

144
00:07:20,200 --> 00:07:20,760
Get out.

145
00:07:20,960 --> 00:07:22,720
I'm helping you
to resolve the issue here.

146
00:07:22,920 --> 00:07:23,840
Alright. Guys.

147
00:07:24,040 --> 00:07:25,720
Please be appeased.

148
00:07:26,400 --> 00:07:28,160
There's no need to resort to this.

149
00:07:29,320 --> 00:07:30,480
Lu, take her outside.

150
00:07:30,488 --> 00:07:31,511
No need for that.

151
00:07:32,160 --> 00:07:33,520
I can leave by myself.

152
00:07:37,040 --> 00:07:37,480
You!

153
00:07:43,520 --> 00:07:46,280
Hello. I'm Xiao Mucheng,
head of Housekeeping Department.

154
00:07:47,360 --> 00:07:50,400
Can I take another sip?

155
00:08:01,333 --> 00:08:03,844
Yi Ran is a member
of the Housekeeping Department now?

156
00:08:04,360 --> 00:08:04,920
Yeah.

157
00:08:05,155 --> 00:08:06,777
The issue would've gone out of hand

158
00:08:06,822 --> 00:08:08,160
without her intervention.

159
00:08:08,200 --> 00:08:10,311
It would go out of hand
with her intervention.

160
00:08:10,640 --> 00:08:11,920
You're mistaken.

161
00:08:12,160 --> 00:08:13,520
It was an urgent situation.

162
00:08:13,622 --> 00:08:15,560
Yi Ran was bold enough
to persuade the guest.

163
00:08:16,240 --> 00:08:17,320
If it were me,

164
00:08:17,600 --> 00:08:18,840
I would've cowered in fear.

165
00:08:18,933 --> 00:08:20,720
I never expected Yi Ran
to be that pitiful.

166
00:08:21,160 --> 00:08:22,520
A playboy cheated on her.

167
00:08:22,577 --> 00:08:24,080
And, she almost got married to him.

168
00:08:27,120 --> 00:08:28,880
Dingdang, say something.

169
00:08:31,920 --> 00:08:33,440
Yi Ran is so pitiful.

170
00:08:43,320 --> 00:08:44,880
I'm annoyed. Don't mess with me.

171
00:08:45,680 --> 00:08:46,600
Who offended you again?

172
00:08:47,280 --> 00:08:47,800
You.

173
00:08:49,120 --> 00:08:50,480
I'm sure it's the God of Plague.

174
00:08:53,377 --> 00:08:54,960
He never appreciated my kind intentions.

175
00:08:56,360 --> 00:08:57,440
If you hate him that much,

176
00:08:57,960 --> 00:08:59,040
why are you working here?

177
00:09:00,120 --> 00:09:02,880
That God of Plague hired me
with a high salary.

178
00:09:02,888 --> 00:09:04,200
He apologized to me sincerely

179
00:09:04,320 --> 00:09:05,520
for what he did previously.

180
00:09:05,640 --> 00:09:06,680
He insisted on hiring me.

181
00:09:07,088 --> 00:09:08,320
I thought he looked pitiful.

182
00:09:08,400 --> 00:09:09,444
That's why I came back.

183
00:09:10,520 --> 00:09:11,880
If you're unhappy with your job,

184
00:09:11,911 --> 00:09:13,160
I'll arrange other jobs for you.

185
00:09:13,622 --> 00:09:15,280
This isn't the only hotel in the city.

186
00:09:15,400 --> 00:09:16,120
What gives?

187
00:09:16,920 --> 00:09:19,280
Why must I be the one
to escape every time?

188
00:09:20,760 --> 00:09:22,680
I want to see what else he's capable of.

189
00:09:23,720 --> 00:09:24,720
Bring it on, then.

190
00:09:25,080 --> 00:09:26,160
I like challenges.

191
00:09:30,800 --> 00:09:31,880
Someone's calling for me.

192
00:09:31,888 --> 00:09:32,888
I'll make a move first.

193
00:09:38,680 --> 00:09:40,040
I've understood the situation.

194
00:09:40,520 --> 00:09:41,480
It wasn't your fault.

195
00:09:43,560 --> 00:09:45,040
It's all Li Lei's fault.

196
00:09:46,560 --> 00:09:47,400
Who's Li Lei?

197
00:09:48,480 --> 00:09:51,000
I thought you had
an ex-husband called Li Lei.

198
00:09:57,680 --> 00:09:59,920
Buddy, don't tell me you fell for it?

199
00:10:00,800 --> 00:10:02,320
Weren't we the ones who got married

200
00:10:02,520 --> 00:10:03,560
and had twins?

201
00:10:12,320 --> 00:10:13,440
Seems like you're fine now.

202
00:10:13,533 --> 00:10:15,111
If so, you have to attend the training.

203
00:10:15,133 --> 00:10:16,688
Report for duty at 9 A.M. tomorrow.

204
00:10:16,800 --> 00:10:17,480
What training?

205
00:10:17,530 --> 00:10:18,466
An employment training.

206
00:10:18,488 --> 00:10:20,755
You need to understand
the hotel's rules, regulations,

207
00:10:20,755 --> 00:10:22,310
and the specific job responsibilities.

208
00:10:22,310 --> 00:10:24,355
Before that, you can only
work here as a part-timer.

209
00:10:24,640 --> 00:10:25,960
There's no need for that.

210
00:10:26,320 --> 00:10:27,520
We're close, aren't we?

211
00:10:27,733 --> 00:10:29,022
Why don't you pull some strings?

212
00:10:29,400 --> 00:10:30,040
I did.

213
00:10:30,600 --> 00:10:33,040
That's why you're here.

214
00:10:34,760 --> 00:10:36,000
Fine. I'll attend the training.

215
00:10:37,040 --> 00:10:37,480
Yi Ran.

216
00:10:38,280 --> 00:10:39,000
I trust you.

217
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:40,800
You can pass it.

218
00:10:41,480 --> 00:10:43,760
God of Plague, thanks for trusting me.

219
00:10:44,800 --> 00:10:45,822
I mean, Vincent.

220
00:10:55,080 --> 00:10:57,080
This will be your dorm in the future.

221
00:11:15,200 --> 00:11:15,960
It's small,

222
00:11:16,400 --> 00:11:17,160
dark,

223
00:11:17,520 --> 00:11:18,840
and has poor space efficiency.

224
00:11:20,040 --> 00:11:21,560
As for the lighting,

225
00:11:23,600 --> 00:11:24,520
it's not that good.

226
00:11:27,440 --> 00:11:28,720
Who said so?

227
00:11:52,440 --> 00:11:53,120
Are you okay?

228
00:11:54,911 --> 00:11:56,800
We have to clean it.
If not, it'll get infected.

229
00:11:57,000 --> 00:11:57,400
Sit down.

230
00:12:20,560 --> 00:12:21,120
Thank you.

231
00:12:24,266 --> 00:12:25,160
What are you doing?

232
00:12:25,644 --> 00:12:27,600
It wasn't good enough. I'm redoing it.

233
00:12:52,120 --> 00:12:53,320
That's more like it.

234
00:12:56,911 --> 00:12:58,160
You should seek treatment.

235
00:13:03,360 --> 00:13:04,840
My poor finger.

236
00:13:09,800 --> 00:13:10,880
The view is great tonight.

237
00:13:47,800 --> 00:13:48,560
Ms. Yi.

238
00:13:48,960 --> 00:13:51,040
Mr. Xiao told me
to call you at this hour.

239
00:13:52,200 --> 00:13:54,177
He said he has arranged
a training for you.

240
00:13:54,177 --> 00:13:55,850
Your wage will be deducted
if you're late.

241
00:13:59,288 --> 00:14:00,400
I'll be there in a second.

242
00:14:00,666 --> 00:14:02,440
And, stop calling me
Ms. Yi in the future.

243
00:14:02,622 --> 00:14:03,422
Just call me Yi Ran.

244
00:14:04,320 --> 00:14:05,800
Alright, Yi Ran.

245
00:14:06,355 --> 00:14:07,844
I'll stop bothering you, then.

246
00:14:12,720 --> 00:14:13,600
Great.

247
00:14:13,622 --> 00:14:16,000
Now, you two will be
running into each other all the time.

248
00:14:17,080 --> 00:14:19,520
What goes around comes around.

249
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:22,400
I'll be honest with you.

250
00:14:23,280 --> 00:14:25,440
You're only able to keep your job
all thanks to Yi Ran.

251
00:14:25,840 --> 00:14:27,240
In the future, we'll be colleagues.

252
00:14:27,400 --> 00:14:29,840
It's better to make another friend
than make another enemy.

253
00:14:51,600 --> 00:14:53,822
You're almost late
on your first day of training.

254
00:14:55,560 --> 00:14:57,320
I'm two minutes early.

255
00:14:59,511 --> 00:15:02,200
I don't care what kind of relationship
you have with Mr. Xiao.

256
00:15:02,533 --> 00:15:04,760
Since he requested me
to train you personally,

257
00:15:05,311 --> 00:15:07,288
I have to clarify several things here.

258
00:15:07,760 --> 00:15:08,720
In our hotel,

259
00:15:09,444 --> 00:15:12,079
you can pretend to be dumb,
but you cannot be dumb for real.

260
00:15:12,080 --> 00:15:14,700
You're not allowed to waste time,
which is more precious than life.

261
00:15:14,800 --> 00:15:17,400
Do not try to find excuses.

262
00:15:17,920 --> 00:15:19,600
And, do not reveal your flaws.

263
00:15:20,120 --> 00:15:20,840
Understood?

264
00:15:22,440 --> 00:15:23,000
Understood.

265
00:15:24,880 --> 00:15:25,400
Good.

266
00:15:26,080 --> 00:15:26,880
Let's begin.

267
00:15:29,977 --> 00:15:31,790
Monitor room status information
in real time.

268
00:15:31,840 --> 00:15:34,000
(Room Status Information)
You should fully understand

269
00:15:34,044 --> 00:15:36,755
the room numbers, names,
and preferences of long-stay guests,

270
00:15:36,777 --> 00:15:38,520
foreign guests, and VIPs to ensure

271
00:15:38,640 --> 00:15:40,840
quick and timely communication
to the floor

272
00:15:40,920 --> 00:15:42,155
and the management personnel.

273
00:15:42,200 --> 00:15:43,440
You should track VIP receptions,

274
00:15:43,488 --> 00:15:44,577
important guest receptions,

275
00:15:44,577 --> 00:15:45,520
and conference receptions.

276
